Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Halve the @lemon{1/2}. Grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @green beans{150} then chop into thirds. Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve and peel the @red onion{1}(halved and peeled) and cut into thin wedges. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Pop the @diced chicken thigh{470} into a #bowl{} with a third of the @Greek style natural yoghurt{150}, half the @korma curry paste{100}, a squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix well and set aside. Pour the @water for the rice{450%ml} into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @basmati rice{225}, lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam). Once cooked, stir half the coriander through the rice.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the brown onion and cook, stirring, until soft and golden, ~{6-8%minutes}. Add the remaining korma paste and garlic and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}. Add the @water for the curry{300%ml} with the @chicken stock powder{1} and mix well. Simmer for ~{5%minutes} until slightly thickened.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high and line a #baking tray{} with foil. Lay the chicken and marinade out on the foil making sure it is spread out evenly. Grill until golden and slightly charred, ~{22-25%minutes}. Turn the chicken halfway.

While the chicken is grilling, add the green beans to the curry and cover with a #lid{} (or some foil) and cook over medium heat until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}. Once the chicken is cooked, transfer to a #plate{}. Pop the green peppers and red onion on the tray, drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper. Spread out to a single layer and pop under the grill until browned, ~{3-6%minutes}.

Reserve 2 portions of the chicken then add the rest to the curry. Add the @baby spinach{125} a handful at a time and stir until wilted. Taste and season with more salt and pepper if you like. Stir the remaining yoghurt and add a splash of water if you like. Divide some of the rice between bowls (reserving the remainder for your lunch wraps) and serve the curry with it. Enjoy!

== Lunch Burrito ==

When you're ready to pack your lunch, mix @mayonnaise{2} with the remaining coriander, a squeeze of lemon juice and season with salt and pepper. Lay the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} between boards, divide the remaining rice between the wraps, top with the reserved chicken and divide the grilled pepper and red onion and spoon over the yoghurt and coriander mixture. Wrap in foil. Refrigerate. At lunchtime, enjoy cold.

> For ultimate freshness, keep the fillings separate and assemble when you are ready to eat them.